Package simulation

Class Individual

  • java.lang.Object
    • simulation.Individual
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    IIndividual

    public class Individual
extends java.lang.Object
implements IIndividual
    Individual is the class that implements IIndividual interface, it overrides the interface methods stating how the actions should be delivered, each new individual is an instance of this class described by:
    • cost - Accumulated cost by traveling along the map, since each edge has a cost of transversing associated;
    • length - Number of edges traveled by this individual;
    • death - Boolean value that indicates if the individual is already death or not
    • path - Map nodes transversed by this individual
    • hs - HashSet used to store the Map nodes already transversed by this individual in this way the program could know efficiently if a node is already on the list or not, saving time compared to searching all the list
    • sim - simulation associated with this individual
    Author:
    Marta Marques (80882), Pedro Direita (81305), Jose Fernandes (82414)

        This class Individual constructor is generally used to generate a new Individual from a parent
        Parameters:
        path - Is a linkedList with the path of the new individual usually a part of the parent path
        hs - HashSet containing all the map nodes in the linkedList path, the HashSet is used for performance improvement
        sim - Simulation where this individual is added, an individual cannot exist alone, an individual is always part of a simulation
        cost - Cost of the initial path given to this individual by its parent
